OL,4,CRail services to come under unified
OL,5,Cstate control
OL,6, The government has announced the
OL,7, biggest shake-up in the UK's railways
OL,8, since privatisation in the mid-1990s.
OL,10,FIt will see the creation of a new
OL,11,Fstate-owned body, Great British
OL,12,FRailways (GBR), which will set
OL,13,Ftimetables and prices, sell tickets in
OL,14,FEngland and manage rail infrastructure.
OL,16,FAfter years of complaints, it aims to
OL,17,Foffer improved services, better value
OL,18,Ftickets and more accountability.
OL,20,FBut private operators will still be
OL,21,Fcontracted to run most trains.
